The paper deals with randomized computations on large data sets, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several computer science sub-disciplines. The most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) since the paper focuses on lower bounds for decision problems such as set equality and multiset equality. The second likely category is cs.DB (Databases) since the paper discusses external memory models and their implications for query evaluation in XQuery, XPath, and relational algebra. The third likely category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity) since the paper deals with randomized algorithms and their performance on large data sets. The fourth likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) since the paper uses mathematical techniques to derive lower bounds for decision problems. The fifth likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory) since the paper discusses the trade-off between internal and external memory space in randomized computations on large data sets.
